info.name: Webhooks Payloads
info.description:
# ü™ù Get started here

Webhooks are a mechanism that allows services to send real-time notifications to your application regarding asynchronous updates. The collection provides endpoints for setting up and managing webhooks, as well as verifying webhook events.

This collection contains examples of webhooks payloads.

## üîñ How to use this collection?

Fork the collection and specify your webhook target endpoint and click "Send". The Postman will send this payload to your target.

Read more about the MaximizerCRM webhooks: [https://developer.maximizer.com/docs/webhooks](https://developer.maximizer.com/docs/webhooks)
